# Generative AI Standards (2026)

## Forbidden Patterns (DEPRECATED)
- NEVER use the `google-generativeai` package. It is legacy.
- NEVER use model IDs `gemini-1.5-flash` or `gemini-1.0-pro`. These are decommissioned.
- NEVER mix `sync` and `async` playwright calls in AI analysis scripts.

## Mandatory Patterns (CURRENT)
- ALWAYS use the `google-genai` SDK.
- **Default model** (local CLI, CI failure analysis, and `DEFAULT_GEMINI_MODEL` in `ai_audit/gemini_client.py`): **`gemini-3.1-flash-lite-preview`** — cost/speed default; matches README, workflow, and CHANGELOG.
- **Optional override:** `gemini-3.1-flash-preview` is allowed when explicitly passed (e.g. `--model`); do not treat it as the project default.
- ALWAYS use `client = genai.Client(api_key=...)` for initialization.

## Enforcement
If you see any legacy Gemini code, STOP and suggest a migration to the 2026 SDK immediately.